M|Prev|tx|In ap rt and Server Actions, start independent operations immediately, even if you don't await them yet.
M|Prev|**In|**
M|Prev|tx|```ts
M|Prev|expo|Request) {
M|Prev|tx|const sn = await auth()
M|Prev|tx|const config = await fetchConfig()
M|Prev|tx|const data = await fetchData(sn.us.id)
M|Prev|tx|return rp.json({ data, config })
M|Prev|tx|}
M|Prev|tx|```
M|Prev|**Co|**
M|Prev|tx|```ts
M|Prev|expo|Request) {
M|Prev|tx|const sessionPromise = auth()
M|Prev|tx|const configPromise = fetchConfig()
M|Prev|tx|const sn = await sessionPromise
M|Prev|tx|const [config, data] = await Promise.all([
M|Prev|tx|configPromise,
M|Prev|tx|fetchData(sn.us.id)
M|Prev|tx|])
M|Prev|tx|return rp.json({ data, config })
M|Prev|tx|}
M|Prev|tx|```
M|Prev|tx|For operations w/ more complex dependency chains, use `better-all` to automatically maximize parallelism (see Dependency-Based Parallelization).